                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12625295" author="sahoo" created="Mon, 25 Aug 2008 09:40:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test case with README&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12625314" author="sahoo" created="Mon, 25 Aug 2008 10:36:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Work around:&lt;br/&gt;
Fortunately, there is a simple work around to this bug. While including the file, use fully qualified path like this:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;_include&amp;gt;${basedir}/osgi.bundle&amp;lt;/_include&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12626073" author="mcculls" created="Wed, 27 Aug 2008 10:58:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe this is because in the manifest goal we&apos;re setting the base directory after processing the instructions - reversing these statements should fix the problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;targeting next major release (1.6.0) of the maven-bundle-plugin&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12626095" author="mcculls" created="Wed, 27 Aug 2008 12:52:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12681195" author="mcculls" created="Thu, 12 Mar 2009 08:05:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing as maven-bundle-plugin 2.0.0 has been released.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
